FT  25 APR 91 / International Company News: Slump at Eaton
Eaton Corporation, the Cleveland-based engineering group, yesterday reported
a net loss of Dollars 12m for the first three months of 1991, down from a
Dollars 54m profit in the period a year earlier, writes Nikki Tait.
First-quarter sales slumped to Dollars 818m from Dollars 942m.
There was a Dollars 39m restructuring charge; without this, Eaton would have
made a Dollars 13m profit.
